liquid.logger

Class LiquidLogger

  • java.lang.Object
    • liquid.logger.LiquidLogger
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interfaceable

    public class LiquidLogger
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interfaceable
    LiquidLogger is the main class of the Logger component. Here, the methods to load or write a log file are initialized. The config file is also read here and stored into a separate variable in the GUI.

    This class interacts with both the GUI and Engine to pass/receive information for the log file.

      • receive

        public void receive(Interfaceable i,
                    GlobalVar.Request request,
                    java.lang.String[] args)
        Method defines requested interactions from the GUI and Engine.

        Current Receive Interactions:
        - LOAD_CONFIG_FILE - receives request to send a self-request to load config data based on file name
        - LOAD_LOG_PARAM - receives request to send a self-request to load parameters based on file name
        - INIT_WRITE_LOG - receives request to initialize process of writing a log file
        - WRITE_LOG_PARAM - receives request to write to log file with the given information

        - WRITE_LOG_DATA - receives information from Engine to write to the log file

        Specified by:
        receive in interface Interfaceable
        Parameters:
        i - - determines which component is requesting an interaction
        request - - determines what interaction is requested
        args - - information required to complete requested interaction
